action.query: EudraCT CDK12/13 inhibitor triple negative breast cancer
EudraCT dinaciclib triple negative breast cancer

content.text:
- **Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer - PubMed** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/`
  - “Here we report the development of **SR-4835**, a highly selective dual inhibitor of **CDK12** and **CDK13**, which disables triple-negative breast cancer (**TNBC**) cells.”
  - “Keywords:  **BRCAness**; **CDK12**; **CDK13**; **PARP inhibitor**; **cisplatin**; intronic polyadenylation; triple-negative breast cancer.”

- **Systematic screening identifies ABCG2 as critical factor underlying synergy of kinase inhibitors with transcriptional CDK inhibitors | Breast Cancer Research** — `https://breast-cancer-research.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s13058-023-01648-x`
  - “These studies have raised interest in combining these inhibitors, including **CDK12/13 inhibitor THZ531**, with a variety of other anti-cancer agents.”
  - “Kinase inhibitor combination screenings were performed to identify kinase inhibitors that synergize with **CDK7 inhibitor THZ1** and **CDK12/13 inhibitor THZ531** in **TNBC** cell lines.”

- **Carrick Therapeutics Announces First Patient Dosed in Phase 1 Clinical Trial of CT7439 (CDK12/13 Inhibitor)** — `https://www.carricktherapeutics.com/news-media/press-releases/detail/25/carrick-therapeutics-announces-first-patient-dosed-in-phase`
  - “the Phase 1 clinical trial evaluating **CT7439**, a novel cyclin dependent kinase 12/13 (**CDK12/13**) inhibitor / **Cyclin-K glue-degrader**.”
  - “Clinical trial details can also be found on www.clinicaltrials.gov under study ID: **NCT06600789**.”

- **CDK inhibition results in pharmacologic BRCAness increasing sensitivity to olaparib in BRCA1-WT and olaparib resistant in Triple Negative Breast Cancer - PubMed** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/38574883/`
  - “Two CDK-inhibitors (CDKi), the broad range **dinaciclib** and the **CDK12-specific SR-4835**, strongly reduced the expression of key HR genes…”
  - “Consequently, both CDKis showed synergism with **olaparib**, as well as with **cisplatin** and **gemcitabine**, in a range of **TNBC** cell lines…”

- **Homologous recombination DNA repair deficiency and PARP inhibition activity in primary triple negative breast cancer - PubMed** — `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32471999/`
  - “within a phase 2 window clinical trial, **RIO trial (EudraCT 2014-003319-12)**, we investigate the activity of **PARP inhibitors** in 43 patients with untreated **TNBC**.”
  - “Following **rucaparib** treatment there was no association of Ki67 change with HR deficiency.”

- **Phase II study of eribulin in combination with gemcitabine… (ERIGE trial) - PMC** — `https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7808100/`
  - “patients with locally advanced BC or **TNBC (ERIGE trial; EudraCT number: 2012-003505-10)**.”
  - “### EudraCT number  **2012-003505-10**.”
